article.headline: Florida A&M 65, Md.-Eastern Shore 55
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Roma Sanders scored 18 points, and Florida A&M defeated Maryland-Eastern Shore 65-55 on Saturday. Darius Glover scored 15 points and added 13 rebounds, and Brian Greene had 10 points for the Rattlers (10-9, 5-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). The Hawks (3-15, 0-6 MEAC) had four players in double figures, but they weren't helped by a poor 32 percent shooting average. Antonio McMillion and Milutin Mirjacic scored 13 points each, and Ed Tyson and Jesse Brooks each added 10 points in the Hawks' seventh loss in eight games. UMES had a five-point lead with 17 minutes to go in the first half. But the rest was all Rattlers, who took a strong lead in the second half after a 16-6 run with about four minutes to go. With 1:06 remaining, Sanders made a free-throw to give FAMU their largest lead of the game at 13.
